Not trying to be rude. But telling me something that doesn't matter doesn't help me at all.

Not trying and actually being rude are two different things. You were being completely rude to people who were just trying to help you out and accidentally glanced over something. I didn't even see it the first time I read that. Additionally, most of the things you were posting doesn't matter at all in trying to troubleshoot your issue. Logs were never posted even after people asked multiple times for them. Please in the future if you run into problems with any mod, don't be spiteful towards people who are just trying to help. I'm glad you got it working but if you need additional help in the future with SVE, post logs, be nice, and be patient.

 

P.S. Thank you to everyone who was offering help since I was not available

Most of the time, they seem to match up fairly well, but when they don't it's very noticable. I imagine it has somewhat to do with trying to map a square texture onto a sphere, but I would think that there might be at least some small room for improvement there as well.

Regardless, still a great addition to the game - I very much look forward to seeing the fully finished product.
